            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Very bad admission process/ experience.... I applied for my daughter's admission.... One the day of test they said she is shortlisted and asked to pay fees .... We didn't pay as some of our queries were not answered and as I rushed back to office..... Later after 3 days when we approached about our queries they said may be ur daughter is not shortlisted and Plz don't come on ur own, we will call.. confused guys......\n\nEspecially the vice-principal is confused and not giving proper clarity....\n\nThe only explanation I find for this is that they are too lazy to keep record of or refer to previous papers/ records (exam happened 3-4 days back)...\n\nNot happy with the experience.... I will obviously not give good review of the school in my society & circle....\n\n1 thing is for sure their infra is v. good but the management's administration is playing spoil-sport...\nHope they improve their act & keep-up the brand of MVN & what it stands for",
